Now here, you're probably intended to stomp the P-switch on that ledge in the lower-right, but that would cause rhinos to rain down onto you, so I'll just use my cape to help me stomp it in midair instead!
Looks like I'm going to tour a grotto... or something...

Change places!

Be sure to grab this P-switch over here before you drop down. Also, I think you're meant to bounce off of this Dino Rhino, but I guess I didn't need to!

Ooh, good thing I had fireballs for that! But, I think you'd be able to bounce off of the next rhino to get over safely if you lacked fireballs. However, you need fireballs to score well on the goal tape.

And here it says, "E". What does this "E" stand for? Elephants, maybe? Do elephants like chocolate? Maybe not as much as peanuts, but what about chocolate-covered peanuts? Is that even a real thing that you can find at your local food store place?
Oops. Turns out I left out 6-A by accident when it came to the "one distinct digit" votes. Fortunately, this didn't affect the outcome.

Apparently, Dino Rhinos and Dino-Torches have no problem with travelling through molten chocolate, so be careful of their flames that they might shoot out of it. However, you can fry them back with fireballs!
Unh! So close! Well, I don't want to waste any more time trying to do that, so I'll just resume the level normally now.
That opens up a path over here that I don't really need. Now, let's go around and see what available levels there are this time...

DOUBLE KILL!

Watch out for the ceiling here.

Oh, nuts. I forgot about that pipe. It leads to the secret exit, and to get into it, you have to be like right there to enter it as soon as it comes on screen. Well, it's no big deal, since I can just get it on my eventual revisit.

Oh, noes. I'm wasting time with this P-switch, and I'm at risk of getting an instant Game Over! No, wait. That's a different hack. Here, as long as you make it past this rhino cage within the 12 seconds that the P-switch lasts, you're fine.

And thus ends the land of chocolate...

Watch your head. Also, try to hold your fire here. If you happen to have a reserve cape (like I do), you might want to switch to it here.

Meanwhile, I've gotta deal with some odd terrain, as well as Dino Rhino Lino Minos, or whatever it is that raocow calls these guys. Be careful of the molten chocolate that defies gravity, but it's okay if just your head touches it (because it's tasty)!
Oh, wait, the "E" was underlined. That must mean it's really important! If anyone can figure out what this "E" is hinting at, let me know!
Note: Only the small rhinos can be cape-thwacked. The big guys are immune to cape spins until you've shrunk them.
Yeah, if you didn't bring a fire flower, and failed to collect any of them from the ? blocks back there, you're screwed (unless you can pull off a wall jump)!
Ah, well, whatever. I figured I'd use my cape to check to see if there were any goodies in the sky to the left of the "E", but I didn't find anything.

However, the big guys are fireproof, but the big guys can't breathe fire either.
